The paper deals with the development of a computational model for perceptual image quality assessment, which involves analyzing visual attributes and human perception. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The model also takes into account efficiency and effectiveness, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the use of visual saliency and contrast as features for image quality assessment involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
